The paper deals with designing mechanisms for eliciting truthful information from agents, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces information monotone functions, which are a mathematical tool for measuring the amount of information contained in agents' reports, and this is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the concept of Bayesian Nash Equilibrium, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
